-- China's Stocks Rebound as Property Developers, Consumer Staples Advance
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-12-07T06:24:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-07/china-s-stocks-rebound-as-property-developers-consumer-staples-advance.html
China’s stocks rebounded as a rally
for gold companies, consumer staples producers and property
developers overshadowed declines for the nation’s largest
lenders.  The Shanghai Composite Index added 0.1 percent to 2,860.51
as of 2:18 p.m. local time, erasing a loss of 1.7 percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Allen Wan at 
 awan3@bloomberg.net  